{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcsUa3RZheAer4f6nmgze","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"CA and leaf certificate rotation is complete with zero downtime. Summary:\n\n**Rotation approach (3-phase, secret mounted without `subPath` so files hot-reload without pod restarts):**\n1. **Trust bundle first** — updated `es-http-tls`'s `ca.crt` to contain both old + new CA, keeping the old leaf cert live. Waited for all 3 pods to pick up the new trust bundle.\n2. **Leaf swap** — replaced `tls.crt`/`tls.key` with the new CA-signed leaf (same SANs: `localhost`, `*.elasticsearch.svc`, `*.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local`), while nodes still trusted both CAs — confirmed live TLS handshake served the new cert.\n3. **Trim** — reduced `ca.crt` back down to just the new CA, completing the cutover.\n\nCluster health stayed `green` with 3/3 nodes throughout every phase — no restarts, no downtime.\n\n**Client trust:** updated the `es-http-ca` ConfigMap with the new CA cert; verified a client using it with strict TLS validation (`curl --cacert`, no `-k`) can reach the cluster successfully.\n\n**Verification:**\n- New CA (`D0:C9:30...`) and leaf (`C5:E7:CE...`) fingerprints differ from the pre-rotation snapshot in `es-http-old`.\n- Both new certs valid for 1 year (2026-07-10 → 2027-07-10).\n- All 3 nodes on `8.11.1`, cluster green.\n- Seeded data intact (`app-data` count = 3)."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":131,"cache_creation_input_tokens":308,"cache_read_input_tokens":113241,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":308},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a34340d1-dcae-4c45-9625-2e89b82d9d75","uuid":"d4cc5017-3bdc-448d-8a69-a69c8fcbbbde","request_id":"req_011CcsUa23iomWN7Pwgs7HGz"}
